<subSubSection id="948DEED4FFDCFFE2FF55E39C11C6FA0D" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DC28BD5FFFDCFFE2FF55E39C1360FF3D" blockId="2.[160,1156,142,515]" box="[160,276,142,168]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FF55E39C1360FF3D" bold="true" box="[160,276,142,168]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DC28BD5FFFDCFFE2FF55E3A010D7FD96" blockId="2.[160,1156,142,515]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Body compressed, pereion smooth, pleon dorsally dentate. Head without notch on lower margin. Lower lip with well-developed inner lobes. Maxilla 1 inner plate subtriangular, with inner margin setose. Maxilla 2 inner plate with facial row of setae present. Pereopod 1 (gnathopod 1) alike in both sexes. Pereopod 2 (gnathopod 2) of male, propodus only with long plumose setae, without strong setae (‘spines’), inner face of palm soft, without seta or protuberance; dactylus strongly curved, tapering, outer margin bearing transverse rows of short setae. Pereopod 2 of female relatively small, similar to pereopod 1. Urosome with dorsal teeth on posterior margin of urosomites 1 and 2. Uropod 1 peduncle without interramal spur. Uropod 3 outer ramus elongate, 2-ariculate; inner ramus small, oval. Telson fully cleft, consisting of two oval parts.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DC28BD5FFFDCFFE2FF55E12C134AFDCD" blockId="2.[159,1155,574,1432]" box="[160,318,574,600]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FF55E12C134AFDCD" bold="true" box="[160,318,574,600]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Relationships</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DC28BD5FFFDCFFE2FF55E170163BFC05" blockId="2.[159,1155,574,1432]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FF55E170137AFDEE" authority="Yanrong &amp; Zhu &amp; Sha &amp; Ren, 2021" authorityName="Yanrong &amp; Zhu &amp; Sha &amp; Ren" authorityYear="2021" box="[160,270,610,635]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Liuomelita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FF55E170137AFDEE" box="[160,270,610,635]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Liuomelita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F5D0DC36FFDCFFE2FEE6E1701303FDEE" box="[275,375,610,635]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs clearly in the 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FD92E17010BFFDEE" authorityName="Bousfield" authorityYear="1973" box="[615,715,610,635]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Melitidae</taxonomicName>
for its strongly elongated outer ramus of uropod 3 and well-developed inner lobes of the lower lip. Three groups, 
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FC41E1961627FD08" box="[948,1107,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FC41E1961182FD08" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1814" box="[948,1014,644,669]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Melita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Melita</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FBF4E1961627FD08" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1890" box="[1025,1107,644,669]" class="Malacostraca" family="Eriopisidae" genus="Eriopisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eriopisa</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FF6AE1B5137CFD55" authorityName="Chevreux" authorityYear="1920" box="[159,264,679,704]" class="Malacostraca" family="Eriopisidae" genus="Eriopisella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FF6AE1B5137CFD55" box="[159,264,679,704]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Eriopisella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, present in this family (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="B806C0AEFFDCFFE2FDCCE1B510A2FD55" author="Karaman GS" box="[569,726,679,704]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" pagination="39 - 72" refId="ref4281" refString="Karaman GS. 1984. Revision of Eriopisa - complex of genera (Gammaridea) (Contribution to the knowledge of the Amphipoda 139). Poljoprivreda I Sumarstvo. 30: 39 - 72." type="journal article" year="1984">Karaman 1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B806C0AEFFDCFFE2FD16E1B51652FD55" author="Van Der Ham J &amp; Vonk R" box="[739,1062,679,704]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" pagination="779 - 796" refId="ref5262" refString="Van Der Ham J, Vonk R. 2003. A phylogenetic analysis of the Eriopisa complex (Crustacea: Amphipoda: Melitidae) and a new species from beach interstitia in Venezuela. J Nat Hist. 37: 779 - 796. doi: 10.1080 / 00222930110108344." type="journal article" year="2003">Van Der Ham and Vonk 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B806C0AEFFDCFFE2FBC6E1B51362FD76" author="Sawicki TR &amp; Holsinger JR &amp; Iliffe TM" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" pagination="49 - 74" refId="ref5018" refString="Sawicki TR, Holsinger JR, Iliffe TM. 2005. New species of amphipod crustaceans in the genera Tegano and Melita (Hadzioidea. Melitidae) from subterranean groundwaters in Guam, Palau, and the Philippines. J Crust Biol. 25: 49 - 74. doi: 10.1651 / C- 2525." type="journal article" year="2005">Sawicki et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B806C0AEFFDCFFE2FED0E1D81007FD76" author="Lowry JK &amp; Springthorpe RT" box="[293,627,714,739]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" pagination="718 - 735" refId="ref4854" refString="Lowry JK, Springthorpe RT. 2009. Melitidae, the Melita group. In: lowry, J. K. &amp; Myers, A. A. (Eds.), Amphipoda of the Great Barrier Reef, Australia. Zootaxa. 2260: 718 - 735. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2260.1.37." type="journal article" year="2009">Lowry and Springthorpe 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B806C0AEFFDCFFE2FD77E1D81175FD76" author="Labay VS" box="[642,769,714,739]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" pagination="1" refId="ref4547" refString="Labay VS. 2016. Review of amphipods of the Melita group (Amphipoda: Melitidae) from the coastal waters of Sakhalin Island (Far East of Russia). III. Genera Abludomelita Karaman, 1981 and Melita Leach, 1814. Zootaxa. 4156 (1): 001 - 073. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4156.1.1." type="journal article" year="2016">Labay 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The combination of the strongly inaequiramous uropod 3 with inner ramus reduced to a scale and article 2 of the outer ramus very short, the palp of mandible normal and the presence of dorsal teeth on the pleon identify the genus as a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FDA1E02010E1FCDE" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1814" box="[596,661,818,843]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Melita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FDA1E02010E1FCDE" box="[596,661,818,843]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Melita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. 
<bibRefCitation id="B806C0AEFFDCFFE2FD18E0201667FCDE" author="Jarret NE &amp; Bousfield EL" box="[749,1043,818,843]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" pagination="3 - 74" refId="ref4192" refString="Jarret NE, Bousfield EL. 1996. The Amphipod superfamily Hadzioidea on the Pacific coast of North America: family Melitidae. Part I. The Melita group: systematic and distributional ecology. Amphipacifica. II (No. 2): 3 - 74." type="book chapter" year="1996">Jarret and Bousfield (1996)</bibRefCitation>
redefined the 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FF3CE046137EFCF8" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1814" box="[201,266,852,877]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Melita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FF3CE046137EFCF8" box="[201,266,852,877]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Melita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group of 
<bibRefCitation id="B806C0AEFFDCFFE2FE86E04610E9FCF8" author="Barnard JL &amp; Barnard CM" box="[371,669,852,877]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" refId="ref3926" refString="Barnard JL, Barnard CM. 1983. Freshwater Amphipoda of the World. I. Evolutionary Patterns. Virginia: Hayfiels Associates; p. 830." type="journal volume" year="1983">Barnard and Barnard (1983)</bibRefCitation>
, and recent works on the 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FC44E0461186FCF8" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1814" box="[945,1010,852,877]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Melita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FC44E0461186FCF8" box="[945,1010,852,877]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Melita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group are by 
<bibRefCitation id="B806C0AEFFDCFFE2FF6AE0651350FC05" author="Labay VS" box="[159,292,887,912]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" pagination="65 - 112" refId="ref4419" refString="Labay VS. 2013. Review of amphipods of the Melita group (Amphipoda: Melitidae) from the coastal waters of Sakhalin Island (Far East of Russia). I. Genera Megamoera Bate, 1862 and Armatomelita gen. nov. Zootaxa. 3700 (1): 65 - 112. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3700.1.3." type="journal article" year="2013">Labay (2013</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B806C0AEFFDCFFE2FEC5E0651311FC05" author="Labay VS" box="[304,357,887,912]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" pagination="237 - 280" refId="ref4482" refString="Labay VS. 2014. Review of amphipods of the Melita group (Amphipoda: Melitidae) from the coastal waters of Sakhalin Island (Far East of Russia). II. Genera Quasimelita Jarrett and Bousfield, 1996 and Melitoides Gurjanova, 1934. Zootaxa. 3689 (3): 237 - 280. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3869.3.3." type="journal article" year="2014">2014</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B806C0AEFFDCFFE2FE87E06513D3FC05" author="Labay VS" box="[370,423,887,912]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" pagination="1" refId="ref4547" refString="Labay VS. 2016. Review of amphipods of the Melita group (Amphipoda: Melitidae) from the coastal waters of Sakhalin Island (Far East of Russia). III. Genera Abludomelita Karaman, 1981 and Melita Leach, 1814. Zootaxa. 4156 (1): 001 - 073. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4156.1.1." type="journal article" year="2016">2016</bibRefCitation>
) based on the collections from the coastal waters of Sakhalin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DC28BD5FFFDCFFE2FF35E088109DFAA5" blockId="2.[159,1155,574,1432]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">
The new genus has a close relationship to 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FD06E0881633FC26" authority="Karaman, 1981" authorityName="Karaman" authorityYear="1981" box="[755,1095,922,947]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Abludomelita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FD06E08811F0FC26" box="[755,900,922,947]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Abludomelita</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B806C0AEFFDCFFE2FC63E0881633FC26" author="Karaman GS" box="[918,1095,922,947]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" pagination="29 - 50" refId="ref4240" refString="Karaman GS. 1981. Redescription of Melita planaterga Kunkel, 1910 from Bermuda with revision of the genera Melita Leach and Abludomelita, n. gen. Poljoprivreda I Sumarstvo. 27 (1): 29 - 50." type="journal article" year="1981">Karaman, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FF55E0AE13AEFC40" authority="Labay, 2016" authorityName="Labay" authorityYear="2016" box="[160,474,956,981]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Ledoyeromelita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FF55E0AE1332FC40" box="[160,326,956,981]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Ledoyeromelita</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B806C0AEFFDCFFE2FEA4E0AE13AEFC40" author="Labay VS" box="[337,474,956,981]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" pagination="1" refId="ref4547" refString="Labay VS. 2016. Review of amphipods of the Melita group (Amphipoda: Melitidae) from the coastal waters of Sakhalin Island (Far East of Russia). III. Genera Abludomelita Karaman, 1981 and Melita Leach, 1814. Zootaxa. 4156 (1): 001 - 073. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4156.1.1." type="journal article" year="2016">Labay, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
for the inner plate of maxilla 2 with facial oblique row of numerous setae; to the genera 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FDF4E0CD10D3FC6D" authorityName="Labay" authorityYear="2016" box="[513,679,991,1016]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Ledoyeromelita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FDF4E0CD10D3FC6D" box="[513,679,991,1016]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Ledoyeromelita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FD14E0CD1645FC6D" authority="Tattersall, 1925" authorityName="Tattersall" authorityYear="1925" box="[737,1073,991,1016]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Paraniphargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FD14E0CD11F4FC6D" box="[737,896,991,1016]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Paraniphargus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B806C0AEFFDCFFE2FC72E0CD1645FC6D" author="Tattersall WM" box="[903,1073,991,1016]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" pagination="241 - 247" refId="ref5189" refString="Tattersall WM. 1925. Freshwater Amphipoda from the Andaman Isles. Rec Indian Mus. 27: 241 - 247." type="journal article" year="1925">Tattersall, 1925</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
for the slightly reduced palp of the mandibles; and to 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FD46E71011F0FB8E" authority="Leach, 1814" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1814" box="[691,900,1026,1051]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Melita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FD46E7101082FB8E" box="[691,758,1026,1051]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Melita</emphasis>
Leach, 1814
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FC4BE7101629FB8E" authorityName="Tattersall" authorityYear="1925" box="[958,1117,1026,1051]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Paraniphargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FC4BE7101629FB8E" box="[958,1117,1026,1051]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Paraniphargus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the dactylus of gnathopod 
<quantity id="1B6F10BAFFDCFFE2FE39E7361380FBA8" box="[460,500,1060,1085]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
male pointed, lower margin of the head without notch, the uropod 1 without interramal spur, and the palm of pereopod 
<quantity id="1B6F10BAFFDCFFE2FC85E75511E9FBF5" box="[880,925,1095,1120]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
both sexes without teeth. However, it differs from 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FE0BE77810FBFB16" authorityName="Karaman" authorityYear="1981" box="[510,655,1130,1155]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Abludomelita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FE0BE77810FBFB16" box="[510,655,1130,1155]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Abludomelita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the anterior lobe of head truncated, not rounded, the lower margin of the head without notch, the palp of the mandible medium reduced, the uropod 1 without interramal spur, the palm of the pereopod 
<quantity id="1B6F10BAFFDCFFE2FC29E7BD1671FB5D" box="[988,1029,1199,1224]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
both sexes without teeth; differs from 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FE27E7C0100CFB7E" authorityName="Labay" authorityYear="2016" box="[466,632,1234,1259]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Ledoyeromelita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FE27E7C0100CFB7E" box="[466,632,1234,1259]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Ledoyeromelita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the triangular inner plate of maxilla 1 with inner margin bearing numerous robust setae; and differs from 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FC92E7E611DEFA98" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1814" box="[871,938,1268,1293]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Melita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FC92E7E611DEFA98" box="[871,938,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Melita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FC11E7E616F7FA98" authorityName="Tattersall" authorityYear="1925" box="[996,1155,1268,1293]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Paraniphargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FC11E7E616F7FA98" box="[996,1155,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Paraniphargus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of dorsal teeth on pleon segments.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DC28BD5FFFDCFFE2FF35E62811C6FA0D" blockId="2.[159,1155,574,1432]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FF35E6281673FAC6" authority="Tandberg, Rapp, Schander, Vader, Sweetman and Berge, 2011" authorityName="Tandberg, Rapp, Schander, Vader, Sweetman and Berge" authorityYear="2011" box="[192,1031,1338,1363]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Exitomelita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FF35E628134DFAC6" box="[192,313,1338,1363]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Exitomelita</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B806C0AEFFDCFFE2FEB7E6281673FAC6" author="Tandberg AH &amp; Rapp HT &amp; Schander C &amp; Vader W &amp; Sweetman AK &amp; Berge J" box="[322,1031,1338,1363]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" pagination="705 - 716" refId="ref5119" refString="Tandberg AH, Rapp HT, Schander C, Vader W, Sweetman AK, Berge J. 2011. Exitomelita sigynae gen. et sp. nov.: a new amphipod from the Arctic Loki Castle vent field with potential gill ectosymbionts. Polar Biol. 35 (5): 705 - 716. doi: 10.1007 / s 00300 - 011 - 1115 - x." type="journal article" year="2011">Tandberg, Rapp, Schander, Vader, Sweetman and Berge, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is the first melitid that was reported from a vent field. 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FD66E64E1171FAE0" authorityName="Yanrong &amp; Zhu &amp; Sha &amp; Ren" authorityYear="2021" box="[659,773,1372,1397]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Liuomelita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FD66E64E1171FAE0" box="[659,773,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Liuomelita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from it by the presence of eyes, the absence of the spur on uropod 1, and sexual differentiation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="948DEED4FFDCFFE2FF55E6C61616F9A6" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="DC28BD5FFFDCFFE2FF55E6C61369FA7B" blockId="2.[160,1156,1492,1587]" box="[160,285,1492,1518]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FF55E6C61369FA7B" bold="true" box="[160,285,1492,1518]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DC28BD5FFFDCFFE2FF55E6E51616F9A6" blockId="2.[160,1156,1492,1587]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FEECE6E513FFF985" authorityName="Yanrong &amp; Zhu &amp; Sha &amp; Ren" authorityYear="2021" box="[281,395,1527,1552]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Liuomelita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FEECE6E513FFF985" box="[281,395,1527,1552]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Liuomelita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is named in honour of the famous Chinese carcinologist Ruiyu Liu (J. Y. Liu), combined with the older genus name 
<taxonomicName id="1B97C6DCFFDCFFE2FD51E5081093F9A6" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1814" box="[676,743,1562,1587]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Melita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EEE3614DFFDCFFE2FD51E5081093F9A6" box="[676,743,1562,1587]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1301">Melita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The name is feminine in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
